The Jamal Adams trade will make or break Jets GM Joe Douglas.

Douglas shipped one of the NFL’s biggest stars to Seattle on Saturday for a boatload of draft capital that he hopes will set a new foundation for the star-crossed franchise.

text:
The Nets won a scrimmage with the Spurs 124-119, showing progress in Orlando.

The Nets shot 43% from the field as a team, and a bright spot, once again, was Rodions Kurucs, who came off the bench at the center position and shot 3-of-3 from downtown.

text:
Florida surpassed New York with 414,511 total coronavirus cases, racing past New York’s 411,200.

The new case total puts Florida at second-highest total in the nation. California currently has more than 440,000.

name: NYDailyNews
text:
Playboy cover girl Bo Black, the wife of Brewers manager Tom Trebelhorn, is dead at 74.

Black, who was adored in her adopted city of Milwaukee for presiding over the annual Summerfest celebration, died in Arizona after a lengthy health decline.
